26/12/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbia's chief war crimes prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic said on Tuesday (December 25th) that in his opinion that Hague war crimes indictee Ratko Mladic is in Serbia, and fugitive Radovan Karadzic is somewhere in the region. The two fugitives will be located, arrested and extradited shortly, Vukcevic told Beta news agency. Commenting on Vukcevic's statement, Serbian Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac said he has no information confirming that Mladic is in Serbia. However, the Serbian Army will act in accordance with the law if the information is confirmed, he said. (Beta, B92, RTRS, SRNA - 25/12/07)
